The website mentions that a Baja Bowl can be ordered with veggies, instead of proteins (meats) and even has a picture of the veggies. It turned out to be a beans and cheese bowl, with 3 pieces of bell peppers, some slivers of white onions. I chose to get the shredded lettuce and pico de gallo to add to my non-existent veggie portion. A sincere request - if you cannot offer real vegetables as an option in your Baja Bowl and quesadillas, please do not put it in your menu. It's very misleading and frustrating at the check out when your staff acts like they have never heard of veggies. I also asked for the roasted green Chile sauce and the server had never heard of it. Bland food and misleading information.

I submitted my experience to the website and was contacted personally by the manager within an hour and a half. She apologized for the wait, explained what has happened and demonstrated a genuinely positive customer service experience. Thank you to the staff and general manager for being great!
